        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-03-05 06:43:55.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\n> pretty sure everything under docs/files should not be committed.\n\nWhat's the problem of these files? Postman collection is crucial for the demo. \nWe wanted to avoid current onap way to document demos in wiki that is not version controlled and most demos are missing important file, yet are always outdated. \n\nI believe that git is only correct place to document official demos.\n\nLogs and postman collections could be zipped, does that help? What is the technical problem here?",
        "patchset_number": 7
      },
      {
        "id": "6aa228ce72e28574f532a36c49ddce5595c5f21e",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5097,
          "name": "Bartek Grzybowski",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "b.grzybowski@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "bgrzybowski"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-03-05 06:58:06.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\nA comment on the json files: since recently Json linters were introduced in this repo so any json file has to obey the rules visible here: https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/integration/+/102593/3/.coafile\nFiles in this review are not passing validation due to inconsistent indentation i guess (indent_size = 2)",
        "patchset_number": 7
      },
      {
        "id": "7866669dc354e58b44c46ee90ecf10a8dd451124",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5550,
          "name": "Konrad Banka",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "kbanka.os@gmail.com",
          "username": "kbanka"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-03-05 07:02:41.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\n(1 comment)\n\n> A comment on the json files: since recently Json linters were\n > introduced in this repo so any json file has to obey the rules\n > visible here: https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/integration/+/102593/3/.coafile\n > Files in this review are not passing validation due to inconsistent\n > indentation i guess (indent_size = 2)\n\nWell, postman environment and collection jsons are put here as natively exported by Postman. Do you think we should add them to exclude rules in .coafile linked?\nIn my opinion it's pointless to edit natively exported json, but maybe it's better if we actually keep aligned with repo rules?",
        "patchset_number": 7
      },
      {
        "id": "61ecc7de3f4813870652fc7cad6db8f304233aa8",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5097,
          "name": "Bartek Grzybowski",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "b.grzybowski@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "bgrzybowski"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-03-05 07:25:54.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\n> Patch Set 7:\n> \n> (1 comment)\n> \n> > A comment on the json files: since recently Json linters were\n>  > introduced in this repo so any json file has to obey the rules\n>  > visible here: https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/integration/+/102593/3/.coafile\n>  > Files in this review are not passing validation due to inconsistent\n>  > indentation i guess (indent_size = 2)\n> \n> Well, postman environment and collection jsons are put here as natively exported by Postman. Do you think we should add them to exclude rules in .coafile linked?\n> In my opinion it's pointless to edit natively exported json, but maybe it's better if we actually keep aligned with repo rules?\n\nI'd urge zipping the json/log files to spare some bits and if not then yes, jsons in that case can be added to ignore rule.",
        "patchset_number": 7
      },
